olive oil
2 potato
1 leek
1 baby broccoli
1 chicken breast strips
½ cream
40 butter
2 milk
1 Chicken-Style Stock Powder
1 Nan's Special Seasoning

• Boil the kettle. Cut potato into bite-sized chunks (peel if you prefer!). Slice
leek.
• Add the boiling water and potato to a medium saucepan. Bring to the boil
and cook potato until easily pierced with a knife, 10-15 minutes.
• In the last 6-8 minutes of cook time, place a colander or steaming basket
over saucepan, then add baby broccoli. Cover with a lid and steam until
tender.
• Transfer baby broccoli to serving plates and season with salt and pepper.
• When the potato is done, drain and return to saucepan.

• While veggies are cooking, heat a large frying pan over high heat with a
drizzle of olive oil.
• When oil is hot, cook chicken breast strips, Nan's special seasoning and
leek, tossing, until browned and cooked through, 4-5 minutes.
• Reduce the heat to medium, then add longlife cream (see ingredients) and
cook until thickened, 1-2 minutes.
• Remove from heat, then season to taste and set aside.

• Add the butter, milk and chicken-style stock powder to the potato. Mash
until smooth.

• Divide mash between plates of baby broccoli.
• Top with chicken and creamy leek sauce to serve.